---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Screen from '../components/Screen.astro';
---

<Layout title="OTA Declaration" wide={true}>
  <Screen>
    <div class="banner">
      <h1>The OTA Declaration</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="page-content markdown-body">
      <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: flex-end; border-bottom: 2px solid #222; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; margin-top: 1rem;">
        <h2 style="border: none; margin: 0; padding: 0;">The Open To All (OTA) Public License™</h2>
        <a href="/web/OTA.md" download class="download-link">Download .md</a>
      </div>
      
      <p><strong>Version 1.0, 22 April 2026</strong><br/>
      Copyleft 🄯 2026</p>
      <p>Everyone is permitted to copy and distribute verbatim copies of this license document, but changing it is not allowed.</p>

      <h3>Preamble</h3>
      <p>The Open To All (OTA) Public License™ is a free, copyleft license for knowledge, documentation, and structural information. It guarantees the end user's freedom to access, study, share, and modify the material, ensuring that knowledge remains a non-rivalrous public good.</p>
      <p>Furthermore, this License enforces a binding ethical framework on the distribution and application of knowledge. It mandates that any system or material covered under this License must be developed and utilized with rigorous professional competence, absolute integrity, and an uncompromising commitment to privacy, fairness, and the safety of the general public.</p>

      <h3>TERMS AND CONDITIONS</h3>

      <h4>0. Definitions</h4>
      <p>"This License" refers to version 1.0 of the Open To All (OTA) Public License™.</p>
      <p>"The Material" refers to any document, software, algorithm, or structural information that contains a notice placed by the copyright© holder saying it is distributed under the terms of this License.</p>
      <p>"You" refers to the licensee.</p>

      <h4>1. Core Freedoms and Public Benefit</h4>
      <p>You are granted the irrevocable freedom to access, study, redistribute, and modify the Material. However, these freedoms are contingent upon your commitment to the public interest. Any application, compilation, or derivation of the Material must prioritize the physical safety, privacy, and well-being of the public. If the Material is utilized in systems posing a credible threat to societal well-being or lacking environmental sustainability, this License explicitly disavows such usage.</p>

      <h4>2. Privacy and Confidentiality</h4>
      <p>The distribution and modification of the Material must align with the principles of Privacy by Design. If the Material constitutes software or infrastructural architecture, it must enforce data minimization, strict role-based access controls, and strong cryptography. You are prohibited from leveraging the Material to erode user privacy or to disclose confidential information unless explicitly required to prevent massive societal harm.</p>

      <h4>3. Fairness and Equity</h4>
      <p>The Material must not be employed to propagate systemic biases or discrimination based on race, gender, sexual orientation, religion, age, disability, or national origin. If the Material pertains to automated decision-making systems or algorithmic modeling, you carry the explicit burden of aggressively testing such derivations for unfair sociological outcomes.</p>

      <h4>4. Competence and Rigour</h4>
      <p>You may only deploy or modify the Material within domains where you possess the necessary technical competence, education, or training. You must not deliberately misrepresent the capabilities, limitations, or environmental footprint of any derivative works. All claims and defect reports regarding the Material must be accurate, rigorous, and strictly based on technical merit.</p>

      <h4>5. Integrity and Intellectual Property</h4>
      <p>Derivatives of the Material must be developed with absolute integrity. You must reject all forms of corruption or conflict of interest in your application of the Material, and rigorously disclose any perceived conflicts to affected parties. Furthermore, while this License grants broad freedoms, it does not permit the unauthorized incorporation of third-party proprietary algorithms, copyrighted© code, or patented concepts without explicit legal authorization.</p>

      <h4>6. Conveying Verbatim and Modified Copies</h4>
      <p>You may convey verbatim or modified copies of the Material in any medium, provided that you conspicuously publish on each copy an appropriate copyright© notice, keep intact all notices stating that this License applies, and give all recipients a copy of this License along with the Material. Any modified versions must be distributed under this exact License (Copyleft🄯 provision).</p>

      <h4>7. Public Domain Dedication of Core Assets</h4>
      <p>To ensure the underlying movement remains immune to intellectual property litigation, the official "Ascendant Monolith" insignia™ and the raw geometric paths constituting the symbol are dedicated to the public domain. No entity may claim exclusive trademark over them.</p>

